a search for stable and long - lived massive particles of electric charge @xmath0  =  1 or fractional charges of @xmath1 , @xmath2 , and @xmath3 is reported using data collected by the opal detector at lep , at centre - of - mass energies from 130 to 209  gev . 
these particles are assumed to be pair - produced in @xmath4 collisions and not to interact strongly . 
no evidence for the production of these particles was observed . 
model - independent upper limits on the production cross - section between 0.005 and 0.028  pb have been derived for scalar and spin-1/2 particles with charge @xmath51 . within the framework of the constrained minimal supersymmetric standard model ( cmssm ) , 
this implies a lower limit of 98.0 ( 98.5 ) gev on the mass of long - lived right ( left)- handed scalar muons and scalar taus . 
long - lived charged heavy leptons and charginos are excluded for masses below 102.0  gev . for particles with fractional charge @xmath52/3 , @xmath54/3 and @xmath55/3 , the upper limit on the production cross - section varies between 0.005 and 0.020  pb . all mass and cross - section limits are derived at the 95% confidence level and are valid for particles with lifetimes longer than 10@xmath6  s.    european organization for nuclear research    cern - ep/2003 - 016 + 11 april 2003    * search for stable and long - lived massive charged particles in @xmath4 collisions at @xmath7  gev *    the opal collaboration +    ( to be submitted to physics letters b ) +    the opal collaboration     g.abbiendi@xmath8 , c.ainsley@xmath9 , p.f.kesson@xmath10 , g.alexander@xmath11 , j.allison@xmath12 , p.amaral@xmath13 , g.anagnostou@xmath14 , k.j.anderson@xmath13 , s.arcelli@xmath8 , s.asai@xmath15 , d.axen@xmath16 , g.azuelos@xmath17 , i.bailey@xmath18 , e.barberio@xmath19 , r.j.barlow@xmath12 , r.j.batley@xmath9 , p.bechtle@xmath20 , t.behnke@xmath20 , k.w.bell@xmath21 , p.j.bell@xmath14 , g.bella@xmath11 , a.bellerive@xmath22 , g.benelli@xmath23 , s.bethke@xmath24 , o.biebel@xmath25 , o.boeriu@xmath26 , p.bock@xmath27 , m.boutemeur@xmath25 , s.braibant@xmath28 , l.brigliadori@xmath8 , r.m.brown@xmath21 , k.buesser@xmath20 , h.j.burckhart@xmath28 , s.campana@xmath23 , r.k.carnegie@xmath22 , b.caron@xmath29 , a.a.carter@xmath30 , j.r.carter@xmath9 , c.y.chang@xmath31 , d.g.charlton@xmath14 , a.csilling@xmath32 , m.cuffiani@xmath8 , s.dado@xmath33 , a.de roeck@xmath28 , e.a.de wolf@xmath34 , k.desch@xmath20 , b.dienes@xmath35 , m.donkers@xmath22 , j.dubbert@xmath25 , e.duchovni@xmath36 , g.duckeck@xmath25 , i.p.duerdoth@xmath12 , e.etzion@xmath11 , f.fabbri@xmath8 , l.feld@xmath26 , p.ferrari@xmath28 , f.fiedler@xmath25 , i.fleck@xmath26 , m.ford@xmath9 , a.frey@xmath28 , a.frtjes@xmath28 , p.gagnon@xmath37 , j.w.gary@xmath23 , g.gaycken@xmath20 , c.geich-gimbel@xmath10 , g.giac